			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">The change I committed (http://src.chromium.org/viewvc/native_client?view=rev&amp;revision=11092) mostly fixes this.

There remains a small race condition: if a call to BreakDebugger() occurs while the debug exception handler is attaching, it might get treated as being from the breakin thread and be ignored.  The real breakin thread's int3 won't necessarily kill the process because in newer versions of Windows it's inside a _try block.

Since this race only occurs in debug builds and not in release builds it doesn't seem worth worrying about.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-04-08T23:48:19.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-04-08T23:48:19.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
			<ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status></ns2:updates><ns0:title>Comment 3 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=2772#c3" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/2772/comments/full/3" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>